summary: The highly anticipated light heavyweight championship bout between Artur Beterbiev and Dmitry Bivol took place this evening, with Beterbiev emerging victorious by majority decision. The fight, which was streamed live on DAZN, was closely contested throughout, with both fighters showcasing their exceptional skills. Beterbiev's relentless pressure and power ultimately proved too much for Bivol, who was unable to mount a consistent offense. The victory cements Beterbiev's status as the undisputed light heavyweight champion, holding all four major world titles in the division.

name: Rocky Elsom
summary: International authorities have issued an arrest warrant for former Australian rugby captain Rocky Elsom. The warrant stems from a French court's conviction of Elsom for failing to fulfill a contract with French rugby club Toulon. Elsom, who played for the Wallabies 75 times from 2005 to 2011 and captained the team on 14 occasions, has been ordered to serve a two-year prison sentence in France. The arrest warrant authorizes law enforcement officials worldwide to detain Elsom and extradite him to France to serve his sentence.

name: Vladimir Putin
summary: Recent reports from Bob Woodward's new book shed light on the relationship between former US President Trump and Russian President Putin. Allegations indicate that Trump secretly sent COVID-19 tests to Putin during the 2020 shortage. Woodward's book also reveals details of Trump's calls with Putin and Biden's private comments. Meanwhile, the Kremlin confirms receiving COVID-19 tests from Trump. Amidst escalating violence in the Middle East, Putin met with Iran's Pezeshkian. Additionally, Trump is said to have continued communicating with Putin after leaving office. Reports suggest that Trump and Putin's bond is closer than previously believed. In response to the Ukraine crisis, the US reportedly implored Putin to avoid using nuclear weapons. Despite celebrating his 72nd birthday, Putin's isolation is evident as birthday greetings remain sparse. The Kremlin, however, refutes rumors of a private phone conversation between Trump and Putin following the Ukraine invasion. Despite this, Putin was celebrated as a "Tsar" in Russia on his birthday.

name: North Korean
summary: Tensions between North and South Korea are escalating, with reports of drone attacks, suspended rail and road links, and accusations of North Korean soldiers fighting alongside Russian forces in Ukraine. Ukraine claims to have hit a North Korean weapons cache in Russia, while North Korea threatens to cut off all roads to the South. South Korea alleges that North Korean soldiers may have been killed in Ukraine, prompting North Korea to issue warnings and accuse South Korea of sending drones into its airspace. Despite these reports, the Kremlin denies the presence of North Korean troops in Ukraine.

name: Brodie Kostecki
summary: Brodie Kostecki, the reigning Supercars champion, has made a remarkable return to Erebus and claimed pole position for the Bathurst 1000 race. Despite tyre vibrations during the top 10 shootout, Kostecki demonstrated his prowess on the track, putting his rivals on notice. In practice, he also dominated the field, showcasing his exceptional skills ahead of the highly anticipated race. During the first laps of the Bathurst 1000 LIVE, Kostecki maintained his lead, while fellow driver Waters experienced a setback by dropping two places. Kostecki's achievement marks a significant milestone in his racing career, etching his name among an elite group of winners.
